# RPC Client Rules

## Fiber JSON-RPC

- Default endpoint: `http://127.0.0.1:8227`
- Single client class in `packages/fiber-rpc`; apps never call `fetch` directly
- Every method: typed params, typed response, timeout, and structured error
- Log request id + method on failure; never log secrets (macaroons, keys)

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
const channels = await fiberClient.listChannels();

// ❌ BAD — raw fetch in a React component
const res = await fetch('http://127.0.0.1:8227', { ... });
```

## CKB RPC

- Testnet RPC lives in `packages/ckb-rpc`
- Use for on-chain channel funding, UTXO, and confirmation context only
- Keep chain queries separate from Fiber off-chain state

## Diagnostics Package

- `packages/diagnostics` consumes fiber-rpc + ckb-rpc; no UI dependencies
- Failure reasons: map RPC/protocol errors → human-readable `Diagnostic` objects
- "Can I Pay?" logic is pure functions where possible — easy to test and reuse in VS Code extension

## Resilience

- Retry only idempotent reads; never auto-retry payment sends
- Handle node unreachable gracefully with actionable UI copy ("Is your Fiber node running on port 8227?")
